olive oil
1 Beetroot
2 Carrot
1 sachet Classic Roast Seasoning
1 packet salmon
¼ tsp Cracked Black Pepper
1 cucumber
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
½ packet Balsamic Glaze
1 packet mayonnaise

•  Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Cut beetroot and carrot into fries.
• SPICY! Peppercorns can be spicy, use less if you're sensitive to heat! In a small bowl, combine cracked black pepper and a drizzle of olive oil.

• Place veggie fries on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle with Aussie spice blend and season.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then bake until tender,
25-30 minutes.

• When the veggies have 10 minutes remaining, pat the salmon dry with paper towel and season on both sides. Spread the peppercorn mixture over the salmon using the back of a spoon.
• Place salmon on a second lined oven tray. Lightly coat or spray with olive oil and bake until the salmon is just cooked through, 8-10 minutes.
• Meanwhile, thinly slice cucumber into half-moons.
• In a medium bowl, add mixed salad leaves and balsamic & olive oil dressing. Toss to coat. Season to taste.

TIP: Patting the skin dry helps it crisp up in the pan!

• Divide peppercorn salmon, spiced veggie fries and cucumber salad between plates.
• Serve with a dollop of mayonnaise. Enjoy!